# src/model/mock.ts contains a literal NUL byte, on purpose: `reqHash` joins its
# request parts with "\n\0\n", and that separator is baked into every recorded
# fixture key in the repo (and into the bundled example-demo recording). It cannot
# be changed without re-keying all of them.
#
# Git auto-detects the NUL and treats the file as binary, so any change to it
# shows up as "Bin 4650 -> 5645 bytes" instead of a reviewable diff. Force a
# textual diff — this changes how the file is *displayed*, never its contents, so
# no hash moves.
